args:
Patia and her fellow Halidom pals took on the
beach-hogging boss of fiends, Barbary, in a
spirited game of beach volleyball. Alas, they
suffered a crushing defeat under the villain's
brutal six-limbed assault.
Afterward, our heroes held a team huddle to\ndebrief and discuss strategies for how best to\nspike the pirate off their beloved beach.
We just need to work on our prideful\nattitudes and lack of skill.
Yes, it appears that beach volleyball\nis far deeper than we first thought.\nThis game demands pure strength.
And yet Barbary's impenetrable defense\ncombined with the constant barrage of\nspikes from her six limbs is staggering.
So we simply need to get STRONGER!\nWe'll train and train until our power is\nsurpassed by no one and nothing!
I don't think we can brute force our way\ninto victory; technique and teamwork\nwill be necessary as well.
It's an overwhelming task, and I'm at a\nbit of a loss as to where to begin.
Good thing I know someone who can help!
If I recall, she's in a nearby town...
...So you were hoping I might divine how\nyou could achieve victory over Barbary?
Anything you can tell us\nwould be most helpful.
Thank you for coming to Lewis Island,\nVerica. We simply must defeat Barbary!

Yes, I sense the strength of your passion.
Very well. All of you look into my
orbuculum and breathe slowly and deeply.
Match your breath with mine.
I see a figure unleashing a mighty spike.\nSuch intensity! One might even go so far\nas to call it...the Omega Shot!
Then mastering this Omega Shot must\nbe the key to defeating Barbary!
It should be, yesâ€”though I've little idea\nhow to actually attempt such a process.
Just knowing where to direct our efforts\nis an important first step.
There's no more time for dawdle, ladies.\nWe begin the training at once!
And where, exactly, are we to train,\nconsidering the beach is overrun?

I may have some thoughts on that subject.
I heard tale from a customer of a location
deep within this island that would make
for excellent training grounds.
Now then, my chickadees! Are you ready?\nPrayers said and mothers kissed goodbye?

The road to learn the Omega Shot will
be one of pain! Of anguish! Of horror!
And only those strong enough to pass will
have the honor to call me master for true!
Verica?! What are you doing here?!
I want to help you realize the future you\nseek. Now stop gawking at me and\nanswer your master, Patia!
Then we begin! As you are all rather soft,\nlet us start with the basics.
Take a ball and bounce it off your forearms\none thousand times without letting it hit\nthe ground. Ready...and BEGIN!
No rest! No lollygagging!\nWHAT DO WE SAY ABOUT THE BALL?!
Exactly! Now keep that up,\nten thousand times!
There's no crying in beach volleyball!\nIf I ask you do to this a million times,\nI expect you to do it with a SMILE!
*pant* We...did it... Ten thousand...\nThink I'm...going to die...
Well done, all of you.\nWell, except for the quitter.
Fate is cruel... I wanted to see it through\nto the end but... F-forigive me...
Her soul has been entrusted to all of you.\nBear her burden as we advance onto\nthe next training session...
A free climb of the cliff!\nNOW GET SOME!
Wait, hold on. We're climbing a cliff \nwithout tools or ropes? Just our hands?!
Master, what in the world does rock\nclimbing have to do with volleyball?

Rock climbing is applicable to ALL sportâ€”
it's a foundational concept among all
knight's armsmasters. THAT'S what it
has to do with this, my little chickadee.
And we'll grow even stronger if we\nattempt it with our bare hands?
What? No, not at all. Free climbing\nis just a hobby of mine.
Listen up, whelps! If you want the Omega\nShot, quit your bellyaching and follow\nalong with me!
*wheeze* Not to question your divine\nwisdom, Goddess Ilia...but why did you\neven see fit to MAKE this cliff...?
Now THAT was a climb! Might even be\non par with the Wall of Despair at the\nWhite Sparrows' training site.
Ah, I've heard plenty of tales about\nthat little man-made beauty!
Wait, so is cliff climbing the secret\nof the White Sparrows' skill?
I do not know...but as I am not a knight...\nI cannot go on...
Tapping out? Very well. I will be sure there\nare always pretty flowers on your grave.\n...The rest of you, with me!
Leave it to me, Estelle! I'll take care of\nthe rest of the plan from here on out!
D-do it... You must acquire...\nthe Omega Shot...
Verica and Estelle's souls go with me.\nWhat is my next mission, master?!
All right, why are there bears here,\nand why are you SO CALM ABOUT IT?!
Prior to this, I took on a request from the\nlocals to deal with some rampaging local\nwildlife and lured them here.
Now, let's teach these toughies a lesson.\nWe'll earn peace for the locals and\nstrengthen ourselves at the same time!
We don't do THIS bare-handed, right?
Of course you doâ€”it's bare-handed\nbear-handling! Observe.
This round of training is done when three\nbears have been taken down. Now then,\nmy chickadees: bust up some bears!
I am a Paladyn, and it is my duty to fulfill\nthe expectations placed upon me.\nBe brave, Julietta!
Nope! Forget it. My stomach can't take this.
Don't be too hard on yourself, Julietta!\nThis very likely isn't a skill you'll ever\nneed in your life as a Paladyn!
Nor you as a White Sparrow, yet here we\nstand. And if you do not accomplish this,\nyou will never be able to defeat Barbary.
You are the last woman standing,\nso your actions here speak for all.
I will do this thing! I swear upon the souls\nentrusted to me by my fellow volleyballers!
Now imagine you have ball in hand and\nattack the bears as you would a spike.
Concentrate the power you need to break\nthrough Barbary's defenses and show me\nyour might!
She did it... But what in the world\nwas that light just now?
That's what I saw in my crystal ball!\nThe Omega Shot!
There's no mistaking it: Our instructor's\nstrict coaching has awakened the power\nwithin Patia.
And this will let us defeat Barbary?
You are a little chickadee no more,\nbut a mighty soaring eagle.
From this day forth, you are the ace of our\nbeach volleyball teamâ€”AND captain!\nDo I hear any complaints?
No! We're counting on you, Captain!
And I accept this duty with gratitude.\nAs ace and captain, I swear to you\nthat my play will bring you pride!
Now get ready, everyone...\nWe have a pirate to pummel!
